Hi Tobi,


thanks for the description of your setup.


Regarding your alternative b) you can use ant and JUnit task [1] with 
fork=On and forkMode=perTest and threads=1 which will trade 
&quot;correctness&quot; for total execution time.
If you write a test class for each time-sensitive test each of them will 
be executed in a seperate JVM and cannot interfere with others regarding 
timeout or memory. Note that this setup will increase total execution 
time because a JVM is started for each test.


Stefan


[1] http://ant.apache.org/manual/Tasks/junit.html


Am 28.07.2014 um 09:09 schrieb Tobias Werth Tobias.Werth@... [junit]:
&gt;
